nals orms today analytics magazine orms tomorrow librarians portal editors cut tutorials about informs member benefits member directory selfservice center governance news room advertising  sponsorship opportunities contact us communities my communities explore our sites pubsonline  healthcare meeting certified analytics professional career center informs connect in this section home explore history of or excellence biographical profiles gomory ralph e ralph e gomory share born may   brief biography ralph gomory is a pioneer in integer optimization who has served as chairman of ibm research’s mathematical sciences department director of research for ibm president of the alfred p sloan foundation and research professor at nyu’s leonard n stern school of business  earlier he spent a pivotal summer at rand and was an andrew dickson white professor at cornell he has been elected to the national academy of sciences the national academy of engineering and the american philosophical society and to the councils of all three societies  in addition to his major contributions to operations research he has written on the nature of industrial research and on global tradegomory originally studied physics at williams college but was drawn to mathematics there and wrote a princeton phd thesis on nonlinear differential equations  after completing his phd he joined the us navy as an officer and was assigned to the physics branch of office of naval research in dc  there he discovered the operations research group org and learned linear programming from alan goldman he remained with org as a consultant after joining the princeton faculty traveling to washington to consult on navy problems  one of these dealt with lp solutions that proposed such oddities as fractional aircraft carriers  he discovered that constraints could be added to the problem that cut away fractional solutions incorporated this cuttingplane approach into an algorithm and proved that it converged to an integer optimum in a finite number of steps his appointment as ibm’s director of research reduced his own research output but he continued to explore the geometry algebra computation and economics of integer programming with new contributions more than  years after his original cuttingplane paperthrough his exposure to org gomory learned of or as “mathematics applied to everyday problems problems of a company scheduling problems etc” and thought “oh that’s what i want to do”  later at ibm he collaborated with coauthors including michel balinski paul gilmore tc hu alan hoffman and others on papers that tackled many core or problems such as the knapsack traveling salesman cutting stock network flow machine sequencing lot size and inventory problems  with gilmore he visited a number of ibm customer sites to understand their problems  at paper mills they hit upon the problem of minimizing waste in cutting a large standardsized roll of paper into a mix of smaller rolls ordered by customers their solution to this practical problem won the lanchester prize in   this work together with his contributions to the theoretical underpinnings of or earned gomory the  john von neumann theory prize awarded by informs he became an ibm fellow the highest honor a scientist engineer or programmer can achieve at the company and moved into management first of the mathematical sciences department and then all of ibm research  during his  year tenure as research head the research division made such technology advances as the singletransistor memory cell highdensity storage devices silicon processing methods the relational database and the risc computer architecture his researchers also won two successive nobel prizes in physicsduring his eighteen years as sloan foundation president the foundation pioneered work on the threat of bioterrorism online learning underrepresented minorities in science and technology the sloan sky survey the census of marine life and the development of the professional science masters degree other biographies profiles in operations research ralph e gomory informs members may access this book for free by logging in for more information about this title and many other springer publications in operations research please click here wikipedia entry for ralph gomoryibm archives ibm builders  ralph gomory accessed november   linkjohnson el   ifors operational research hall of fame ralph e gomory international transactions in operations research    linknyu stern business school faculty profile ralph gomory accessed november   linkralphgomorycom bio ralph e gomory accessed november   link education williams college ba cambridge universityprinceton university phd  mathematical genealogy affiliations academic affiliations cornell university new york university polytechnic inst of polytechnic inst of brooklyn princeton university nonacademic affiliations ibm u s navy alfred p sloan foundation key interests in orms methodologies combinatorial optimization computer networks and systems economics  econometrics inventory management  production planning mathematical programming optimization theory application areas manufacturing  service operations rd and product development oral histories r e gomory  interview by william thomas july  alfred p sloan foundation new york transcript memoirs and autobiographies memoirs gomory re  early integer programming oper res – awards and honors lanchester prize john von neumann theory prize ieee ernst weber engineering leadership recognition national medal of science heinz award for technology the economy and employment the institute for operations research and the management sciences fellow harold lardner prize  selected publications gomory e e  essentials of an algorithm method for integer solutions to linear programs bulletin of the american mathematical society  gomory r  an algorithm for the mixed integer problem no randp rand corporation santa monica cagomory r e  solving linear programming problems in integers comb