enormous eyebrows and clownlike lipstick bette davis as a shaky old woman with a cigarette elizabeth taylor at  pounds or any aging actress after too many plastic surgeries these actresses burst onto the hollywood scene as beautiful young women and they should be remembered as the gorgeous girls that they were we want everyone to experience the beauty of these women to encourage you to watch their old movies and to fall in love with them as moviegoers did when they were young dame of the day ann sheridan the oomph girls “they nicknamed me the oomph girl and i loathe that nickname just being known by a nickname indicates that youre not thought of as a true actress” most beautiful classic actresses of all time s   ♥   s   ♥   s  ♥   s  marilyn monroe s icons “i want to be a big star more than anything its something precious”    hedy lamarr the most beautiful woman in films “any girl can be glamorous all you have to do is stand still and look stupid”    elizabeth taylor lizs “ive only slept with the men ive been married to how many women can make that claim”    greta garbo the faces “i never said i wanted to be alone i said i want to be left alone”    audrey hepburn s sweethearts “i dont have sex appeal and i know it as a matter of fact i think im rather funny looking my teeth are funny for one thing and i have none of the attributes usually required for a movie queen including the shapeliness”    ava gardner s beautys “what id really like to say about stardom is that it gave me everything i never wanted deep down im pretty superficial”    grace kelly gracies “hollywood amuses me holierthanthou for the public and unholierthanthedevil in reality”    jean harlow baby or the platinum blondes “men like me because i dont wear a brassiere women like me because i dont look like a girl who would steal a husband at least not for long”    gene tierney s movie stars “i dated dozens of young men had fun with all made commitments to none”    rita hayworth the love goddesss “i think all women have a certain elegance about them which is destroyed when they take off their clothes”    carole lombard the profane angel the hoosier tornados “ive lived by a mans code designed to fit a mans world yet at the same time i never forget that a womans first job is to choose the right shade of lipstick”    sophia loren s movie stars “many people think they want things but they dont really have the strength the discipline they are weak i believe that you get what you want if you want it badly enough”    louise brooks lulu or brooksies “love is a publicity stunt and making love  after the first curious raptures  is only another petulant way to pass the time waiting for the studio to call”    brigitte bardot bbs “i gave my beauty and my youth to men i am going to give my wisdom and experience to animals”    natalie wood natasha s “you get tough in this business until you get big enough to hire people to get tough for you then you can sit back and be a lady”    loretta young attila the nun saint lorettas “a face that is really lovely in repose can fall apart if when its owner starts to talk she distorts every feature”    lana turner sweater girls “a successful man is one who makes more money than a wife can spend a successful woman is one who can find such a man”    marlene dietrich lili marlenes “the legs arent so beautiful i just know what to do with them”    ingrid bergman s iconic actresss “i can do everything with ease on the stage whereas in real life i feel too big and clumsy so i didnt choose acting it chose me”    clara bow the it girls “we had individuality we did as we pleased we stayed up late we dressed the way we wanted”    jane russell s movie stars “sometimes the photographers would pose me in a lownecked nightgown and tell me to bend down and pick up the pails they were not shooting the pails”    vivien leigh vivlings “some critics saw fit to say that i was a great actress i thought that was a foolish wicked thing to say”    joan crawford billie or cranberrys “womens lib poor little things they always look so unhappy have you noticed how bitter their faces are”    ginger rogers s movie stars “im most grateful to have had that joyous time in motion pictures it really was a golden age of hollywood pictures were talking they were singing they were coloring”    joan fontaine s beautiful actresss “the main problem in marriage is that for a man sex is a hunger if he is hungry and cant get to a fancy french restaurant hell go to a hot dog stand”    jennifer jones s movie stars “if you could choose one characteristic that would get you through life choose a sense of humor”    claudette colbert lilys “i think there was more sex in those old films than in all that thrashing around today s im tired of sex scenes”    kim novak s movie stars “i loved acting which was never about money the fame it was about a search for meaning it was painful”    joan collins the british opens “the problem with beauty is that its like being born rich and getting poorer”    myrna loy queen of hollywood the perfect wifes “some perfect wife i am ive been married four times divorced four times have no children and cant boil an egg”    mary pickford baby gladys the glad girls “it would have been more logical if silent pictures had grown out of the talkies instead of the other way around”    susan hayward s movie stars “you aim at all the things you have been told that stardom meansthe rich life the applause the parties then you find that you have it all and it is nothing really nothing”    fay wray the queen of screams “as soon as i got off the boat a man met me and said will you please come up to the bbc studios and scream for us”    veronica lake the peekaboo girls “hollywood gives a young girl the aura of one giant selfcontained orgy farm its inhabitants dedicated to crawling into every pair of pants they can find”    barbara stanwyck missys “im a tough old broad from brooklyn i intend to go on acting until im ninety and they wont need to paste my face with makeup”    jayne mansfield s movie stars “my father was the only man i ever knew who really loved me unselfishly who never used me for personal gain”    thelma todd hot toddy the ice cream blondes  marion davies s film comedienne and philanthropists “with me it was  talent and  publicity”    bette davis the fifth warner brother or the first lady of films “an affair now and then is good for a marriage it adds spice stops it from getting boring i ought to know”    lillian gish the first lady of american cinemas “i think the things that are necessary in my profession are these taste talent and tenacity i think i have had a little of all three”    jeanne crain hollywoods number one party girls “i loved being at the studio th centuryfox after all i started at  and i grew up there”    betty grable the pinup girl or the girl with the million dollar legss “putting women on pedestals began to die out when it was discovered they could give orders better from there”    diana dors the siren of swindon or hurricane in minks “i was the first homegrown sex symbol when marilyn monroes first film was shown a columnist wrote how much like our diana dors she is”    lauren bacall baby or the looks “men need to feel important they feel better when theyre with younger girls or unknown girls”    linda darnell tweedless “people got tired of seeing the sweet young things i was playing and i landed at the bottom of the roller coaster id crammed thirty years into teni missed out on my girlhood the fun little things that now seem important”    mae west s movie stars “good girls go to heaven bad girls go everywhere else”    katharine hepburn kate and first lady of cinemas “if you want to sacrifice the admiration of many men for the criticism of one go ahead get married”    maureen osullivan s movie stars “i dont think i ever got parts that interested me well i did occasionally but more often than not they did not interest me”    lucille ball queen of the bss “once in his life every man is entitled to fall madly in love with a gorgeous redhead”    carole landis the ping girls “i want to be as good an actress as bette davis and id like to be a great singer but more than that id like to be happily married and have some children”    shirley maclaine s movie stars “i was always a character actress and never a sex symbol even when i was the leading lady i was a character actor”    ann sheridan the oomph girls “they nicknamed me the oomph girl and i loathe that nickname just being known by a nickname indicates that youre not thought of as a true actress”    olivia de havilland livvies “playing good girls in the s was difficult when the fad was to play bad girls actually i think playing bad girls is a bore i have always had more luck with good girl roles because they require more from an actress”    vilma banky the hungarian rhapsodys “for the love scenes in my first hollywood silent picture i spoke in hungarian and my costar chatted about cricket and kippers”    ella raines s movie stars  margaret lindsay s movie stars “the little things are most worthwhile quiet word a look a smile”    judy garland s entertainers “in the silence of night i have often wished for just a few words of love from one man rather than the applause of thousands of people”    joan blondell s sexy wisecrackers “it amazes me how some of these little numbers with dreamy looks and a dead pan are getting away with not acting ”    jane wyman s movie stars “i dont know why id have to cooperate because he knows everything i know im just going to live my life and have fun”    dorothy lamour the beautiful one or dotties “glamor is just sex that got civilized a pretty girl tastefully posed in a scant costume is even a sort of cultural achievement”    barbara lawrence s movie stars  ann sothern s movie stars “we were just big namesthe products of a good publicity department todays crop of actresses and actors have real talent good looks are no longer an essential part of the busi